  "notes": "Copernicus SAR mission. Seeded for the Orbits surface on Florian's instruction (2026-07-05); fields await sourced fill by the weekly maintenance run. ESA confirmed Sentinel-1A's operational duties ended 29 June 2026 (disposal phase to begin over summer 2026), leaving Sentinel-1C and Sentinel-1D as the active pair; Sentinel-1B was already lost in 2021. eoPortal states non-square resolutions per mode (range x azimuth); those figures are kept verbatim in the mode names rather than reduced to one number.",
